Package com.github.rschmitt.collider

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClojureList<T>
    A generic persistent immutable List implementation, with three types of methods: Read methods from List, such as ClojureList.get(int) Write methods from List, such as ClojureList.add(T); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException and have been marked as @Deprecated Persistent "modification" methods, such as ClojureList.append(T); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current list
    ClojureMap<K,V>
    A generic persistent immutable Map implementation, with three types of methods: Read methods from Map, such as ClojureMap.get(java.lang.Object) Write methods from Map, such as ClojureMap.put(K, V); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException and have been marked as @Deprecated Persistent "modification" methods, such as ClojureMap.assoc(K, V); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current map
    ClojureSet<T>
    A generic persistent immutable Set implementation, with three types of methods: Read methods from Set, such as ClojureSet.contains(java.lang.Object) Write methods from Set, such as ClojureSet.add(T); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException and have been marked as @Deprecated Persistent "modification" methods, such as ClojureSet.with(T); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current set
    Collider
    A collection of factory methods to create immutable collections.
    TransientList<T>
    A list that can be modified in-place and then converted to a ClojureList in O(1) time.
    TransientMap<K,V>
    A map that can be modified in-place and then converted to a ClojureMap in O(1) time.
    TransientSet<T>
    A set that can be modified in-place and then converted to a ClojureSet in O(1) time.
